-- ── Budgie ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Budgie, formally Budgie Desktop, is a free and open-source desktop environment for Linux and other Unix-like operating systems, built around a traditional desktop metaphor with an emphasis on simplicity, elegance, and light resource usage. It was created by developer Ikey Doherty, first announced in December 2013 and publicly released in February 2014 as the default desktop for his EvolveOS distribution, which was later renamed Solus. Budgie initially borrowed heavily from GNOME's underlying components while presenting a more conventional desktop layout than GNOME Shell, and it introduced a distinctive feature called Raven, an all-in-one sidebar that consolidates notifications, a calendar, media playback controls, volume adjustment, and system resource monitoring in one place. After years as Solus's flagship desktop, Budgie became an independent project in January 2022 under a new organization called Buddies of Budgie, following lead developer Joshua Strobl's departure from Solus. The project is now undergoing a major re-architecture with Budgie 11, rebuilt from the ground up using Qt6 and C++ with a modular core and pluggable shell design intended to carry the desktop environment forward for the next decade. Budgie is available as the default environment on Solus and as the official Ubuntu Budgie flavor of Ubuntu, and is also packaged for Manjaro, EndeavourOS, Arch Linux, Debian, and several other distributions. Being free and open-source software, Budgie has no purchase price or subscription plans.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Free and open source (no cost, no subscription tiers)$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$1-10 (volunteer and community-driven open-source project; not a commercial company)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Not applicable - open-source project with no corporate headquarters; the Buddies of Budgie organization coordinates development$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Budgie Desktop Review 2026: The Linux Desktop Environment Explained$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Budgie Desktop is a free, open-source Linux desktop environment known for its Raven sidebar and traditional layout. See its history, features, and where to get it.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Budgie, more formally known as Budgie Desktop, is a free and open-source graphical desktop environment for Linux and other Unix-like operating systems, designed around a familiar, traditional desktop metaphor rather than the more radically reworked interfaces of some other modern desktop environments. The project traces its origin to December 14, 2013, when developer Ikey Doherty announced he was building it as the default desktop for a new Linux distribution he was creating called EvolveOS. The first public release of Budgie followed on February 17, 2014. EvolveOS was subsequently renamed Solus, and Budgie became Solus's signature, flagship desktop environment, closely tied to the distribution's identity for most of the following decade. In its early architecture, Budgie deliberately borrowed underlying components and technologies from the GNOME desktop project, since building a desktop environment entirely from scratch would have been an enormous undertaking, but it wrapped those components in a more conventional panel-and-menu layout that felt more familiar to users coming from Windows or older desktop paradigms than GNOME Shell's more unconventional interface. Development moved quickly in Budgie's early years, including a significant release, Budgie 8, in November 2014 that added a redesigned, usage-sorted application menu, panel auto-hide behavior, quicklist support, and the ability to pin applications. By December 2015, Budgie reached version 10, which represented a full rewrite of the codebase in the Vala programming language, a milestone release that shaped the architecture the desktop ran on for years afterward. One of Budgie's most distinctive and frequently highlighted features is Raven, an all-in-one sidebar panel that consolidates several functions that might otherwise be scattered across separate applets: notifications, a calendar view, media playback controls, volume and audio adjustment, and system resource monitoring, all accessible from a single consistent panel without cluttering the desktop itself. As Budgie matured, its adoption spread well beyond Solus. SparkyLinux and Manjaro added Budgie options in 2015; Arch Linux, Ubuntu, and Void Linux followed with their own Budgie packages or editions in 2016. The Ubuntu-based variant eventually became Ubuntu Budgie, which Canonical adopted as an official recognized flavor of Ubuntu, giving Budgie one of its most visible and widely used distribution channels outside of Solus itself. A major organizational shift occurred on January 1, 2022, when Joshua Strobl, who had become Budgie's lead developer, resigned from the Solus project and established a new, independent organization called Buddies of Budgie to steward the desktop environment going forward, decoupling Budgie's development from any single Linux distribution. Since then, the project has been working on Budgie 11, described as a fundamental re-architecture of the desktop environment, moving the codebase from Vala and GTK-era foundations to Qt6 and C++, with a modular core and a pluggable shell architecture intended to make the desktop more maintainable and adaptable for the next decade of development, rather than an incremental update to the existing Vala-based codebase. As with essentially all Linux desktop environments, Budgie is entirely free and open source, distributed with no purchase price, license fee, or subscription plan of any kind; anyone can download, use, modify, and redistribute it under its open-source license, and it is maintained by volunteer and community contributors coordinated through the Buddies of Budgie organization rather than a commercial company with paid staff.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '85ea5bd3-d7d0-4431-bd52-9819c2698a09';

